<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
MHD_unescape_plus calls strchr(arg, '+') and then writes to *p when a '+' is found. strchr scans forward until it finds a '\0' terminator. The code that calls MHD_unescape_plus (MHD_parse_arguments_) assumes that the args string is null-terminated, but there is no explicit bound or length passed to strchr/MHD_unescape_plus. If the buffer pointed to by args is not properly null-terminated inside its allocated object (for example if the request-target/query substring is at the very end of the input buffer and no '\0' was written), strchr may read past the end of the object searching for '\0' and the subsequent write (*p = ' ') may modify memory beyond the object. In that scenario use of the string.h routine strchr (via MHD_unescape_plus) results in accesses beyond the bounds of the object and thus violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
